Award winning Afrobeats artist, Davido hit London’s Heathrow Airport this morning on a British Airways flight for his 30 billion UK Tour. He was welcomed by the organizers of the tour, Smade Entertainment. The 30 billion UK tour will visit 6 cities in the UK including Leicester on the 14th of February at The Athena, Dublin on the 15th of February at The Academy, Manchester on the 16th of February at History Manchester, Birmingham on the 17th of February at The New Bingley Hall, London on the 18th of February at The 02 Academy before rounding up in Hertfordshire on the 19th of February at Forum Hertfordshire University. With the Dublin and London legs of the tour already sold out, the anticipation is high for what is sure to be an exciting time for Davido’s UK fans.